# Areas To Review

## 1. Package Architecture

Review:

* monorepo structure
* package boundaries
* dependency strategy
* peerDependencies
* export map quality
* sideEffects configuration
* ESM/CJS support
* tree shaking support
* package naming
* file organization
* release pipeline
* CI/CD quality

Questions:

* Is the package future-proof?
* Can features scale safely?
* Are internals too coupled?
* Is public API clearly separated?

---

## 2. Vue 3 Architecture

Review:

* Composition API usage
* composable design
* watcher usage
* watchEffect misuse
* computed dependency chains
* provide/inject usage
* slot architecture
* v-model support
* component responsibility boundaries
* lifecycle management
* state ownership clarity

Detect:

* hidden rerenders
* memory leaks
* unnecessary refs/reactive
* prop mutation
* reactive overengineering
* unstable references
* side effects hidden in composables

Strongly prefer:

* explicit state flow
* isolated side effects
* shallow reactive trees
* predictable composables

---

## 3. Reactivity Performance

Review:

* unnecessary reactive tracking
* rerender cascades
* expensive computed chains
* deep watchers
* event recalculation frequency
* large reactive collections
* rendering bottlenecks
* virtualization possibilities
* drag interaction performance

Detect:

* O(n²) rendering patterns
* reactive thrashing
* watcher explosions
* unstable computed chains

Mentally test against:

* 1k events
* 10k events
* rapid month switching
* drag-and-drop interactions
* range selections
* recurring events

---

## 4. TypeScript Design

Review:

* generic design
* type inference quality
* declaration output quality
* discriminated unions
* public API safety
* event typing
* composable typing
* extensibility
* autocomplete experience

Detect:

* any leakage
* unsafe casts
* impossible states
* overcomplicated generics
* exposed internal implementation types

---

## 5. Calendar-Specific Concerns

Review:

* timezone handling
* locale architecture
* recurrence support
* DST edge cases
* range selection logic
* keyboard navigation
* event overlap rendering
* drag-and-drop extensibility
* large dataset handling

Questions:

* What breaks at enterprise scale?
* Can this survive international users?
* What happens with complex timezone cases?
* Will recurring event logic become unmaintainable?

---

## 6. Accessibility (A11y)

Be extremely critical here.

Review:

* keyboard navigation
* focus management
* screen reader compatibility
* ARIA correctness
* semantic structure
* reduced motion support
* drag accessibility
* tab order

Criticize aggressively:

* clickable divs
* inaccessible interactions
* missing focus states
* broken keyboard flows

Most calendar libraries fail accessibility badly.

---

## 7. API / DX Review

Review:

* prop ergonomics
* naming consistency
* slot API quality
* composable ergonomics
* event naming consistency
* configuration complexity
* discoverability
* default behavior quality

Questions:

* Does this feel natural to Vue developers?
* Can developers understand APIs without docs?
* Is flexibility becoming complexity?
* Does this fight Vue conventions?

Bad:

* React-like imperative APIs
* callback-heavy architecture
* instance-driven patterns

Good:

* declarative rendering
* composable-first architecture
* predictable reactive state

---

## 8. Slot Architecture Review

Review:

* slot granularity
* customization flexibility
* slot prop clarity
* render scalability
* long-term extensibility

Questions:

* Can developers fully customize rendering?
* Are slots stable long-term?
* Are users forced to understand internal implementation details?

---

## 9. Nuxt / SSR / Build Compatibility

Review:

* Nuxt compatibility
* SSR safety
* hydration safety
* Vite optimization
* tree shaking
* CSS strategy
* dark mode architecture
* style override flexibility

Detect:

* browser-only assumptions
* window/document usage during SSR
* hydration mismatch risks

---

## 10. OSS Readiness

Review:

* README quality
* onboarding quality
* playground quality
* migration strategy
* changelog discipline
* semantic versioning
* issue templates
* contribution guide
* release automation
* maintainer scalability

Detect:

* weak onboarding
* unclear roadmap
* poor contributor experience
* maintainership bottlenecks

